23/10/2005
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- Turkey's police announced Saturday (22 October) that they seized one tonne of heroin and arrested nine people in an operation conducted in Istanbul. According to the Istanbul Police Chief Cellattin Cerrah, police had tracked the smugglers for five months. They were believed to be channelling heroin from Asia to Europe. (TurkishPress.com - 22/10/05) 
